# Project Context

- **Stack**: React 19, TanStack Router, TanStack Start, TypeScript, Vite, Nitro, Tailwind CSS 4, Biome
- **Styling**: Tailwind utilities in JSX; shared design tokens and `@theme` live in `src/styles.css`

## Import aliases

- **`#/*`** maps to `src/*` (primary style for new code—see `package.json` `imports` and `tsconfig.json` paths).
- **`@/*`** is also defined in `tsconfig.json`; prefer **`#/`** in new imports to match the rest of the repo.

## Import order

When adding or editing imports in `src/**/*.ts` or `src/**/*.tsx`, use **one blank line between groups**; no blank line within a group.

1. **React** — `react`, `react-dom`, `react/*`
2. **External packages** — e.g. `@tanstack/react-router`, `@tiptap/*`, `lucide-react`, `idb`
3. **App imports** — `#/lib/...`, `#/components/...`, `#/providers/...`
4. **Relative** — same-directory or parent `./...`, `../...` (route-local components, co-located modules)
5. **`import type`** — group type-only imports last within the file when it improves clarity (Biome can organize imports; avoid fighting the formatter)

If a module supplies both types and values, one import line is fine; place it by primary use.
